# ğŸ§  Real-Time Stop Sign Detection with UART Control(RTCV)

A Python-based real-time computer vision system that uses a webcam to detect **stop signs**, sends a **UART signal** to an Arduino to control a robot's behavior, and logs detection frames. Designed for robotics and embedded control demonstrations.

---

### ğŸŒŸ Features

âœ… Real-time webcam detection  
âœ… Stop sign recognition using Haar Cascades  
âœ… Simulated UART communication (Arduino optional)  
âœ… Auto-saving of detected stop sign frames  
âœ… "Stop Sign Detected" overlay for 3 seconds  
âœ… Throttled UART '0' messages (twice per second)  
âœ… Multithreaded control for smooth real-time behavior

---

### ğŸš¦ Project Description

This project simulates an intelligent robot equipped with a camera that can:

- ğŸ›‘ **Detect stop signs** in real-time using OpenCV and Haar cascade.
- ğŸ” **Send UART commands** to an Arduino to control motion:
  - Sends `'1'` to stop the robot (for 3 seconds).
  - Sends `'0'` continuously to keep moving.
- ğŸ’¾ **Capture and save frames** of stop signs for logging or training (stored in `/data` folder).
- ğŸï¸ **Overlay visual feedback** ("Stop Sign Detected") on video feed during stop period.

---

### âš™ï¸ System Functionalities

| Component             | Description                                                                        |
| --------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| ğŸ–¼ï¸ Vision System     | Uses a webcam feed and Haar cascade classifier to detect stop signs in live video. |
| ğŸ§  Decision Logic     | Triggers a stop signal (`'1'`) for 3 seconds when a stop sign is detected.         |
| ğŸ“¤ UART Communication | Sends data over serial (currently commented for testing without hardware).         |
| ğŸ’¾ Data Logging       | Saves images of detected stop signs with timestamps in the `data/` folder.         |

